    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1819-12-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1819-12-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="109"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d109">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">McCulloch</persName>, collector, to
                        Captain <persName type="to">Webster</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Custom-House, Baltimore</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Collector’s Office</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1819-12-03">
                        <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 3, 1819</date>.</dateline>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Upon receiving this be pleased to attend the
                    South American schooner El Ameida till she goes out of the Chesapeake. You will
                    anchor near her when she anchors, and keep off all boats or vessels visiting her
                    and prevent anything being *carried on board her from the water or land side
                    that will add to her military strength. <pb facs="0514" n="500" xml:id="pg_500"
                    /> The necessary supplies of fresh provisions and water and vegetables are not
                    intended to be denied, but men and warlike stores must be driven off or seized.
                        <seg type="margin">[132]</seg>
                </p>
                <p>If the inspector meet you he will give you the commission and clearance of the
                    vessel, which you will please deliver to her commander at her departure.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>J. H. McCULLOCH.</item>
                            <item>Captain <hi rend="smallcaps">John A. Webster.</hi>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
